                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="33473" author="david_syer" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2008 05:51:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think this fix was very successful - clearly null is not Serializable, so it just fails in another way.  A unit test should have caught this?  See the same forum post for the result.  What is causing the null to be inserted in the first place?  Is it a database platform issue?  Can they be ignored?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="33476" author="lucas.l.ward" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2008 07:02:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like I accidentally created a duplicate with &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/BATCH-483&quot; title=&quot;ExecutionContext does not handle null values correctly&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BATCH-483&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BATCH-483&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem in the specific forum post I have seen is that the JdbcCursorItemReader stores &apos;skipped lines&apos; as statistics in the execution context.  However, if there are no skipped lines, that will be empty, which the repository will attempt to pass in as null when recreating the context.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="33478" author="lucas.l.ward" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2008 07:15:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I closed &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/BATCH-483&quot; title=&quot;ExecutionContext does not handle null values correctly&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BATCH-483&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BATCH-483&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with a fix for the ExecutionContext.  This issue can be used to track that we&apos;re properly testing our readers and writers in restart scenarios.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="33506" author="robert.kasanicky" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2008 21:01:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think we need additional tests for repository (or daos) rather than readers/writers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="33508" author="david_syer" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2008 21:19:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Agreed.  The errors reported by users here appear to originate in the way the database platform treats empty String.  I think we can close this issue again and raise another one for a CI build against various database platforms (unlikely to happen before 1.0) - see &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/BATCH-488&quot; title=&quot;CI builds against various database platforms&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BATCH-488&quot;&gt;BATCH-488&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
